# <gitmoji> <type>: <title>

# Title: include issue number, max 50 characters on one line
# ------------------------------------------------|
# Body: max 72 characters per line
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------|
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------|
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------|
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------|

# ------------------

# Rules:
# - Write the title as an imperative sentence (e.g., "Add feature", "Fix bug")
# - Title must be 50 chars or less, no trailing punctuation
# - Separate title and body with a blank line
# - Body should explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW)
# - Body lines must be 72 chars or less
# - Footer for additional info (BREAKING CHANGE, related issues, etc.)

# ------------------

# <type> list
# ✨ feat:       Add a new feature
# 🐛 fix:        Fix a bug
# ♻ refactor:    Refactor code without changing functionality
# 💄 style:      UI/style changes (no logic changes)
# 📝 docs:       Documentation changes
# ✅ test:       Add or modify tests
# 🔨 chore:      Minor changes
# 🚀 perf:       Performance improvements (speed, memory, etc.)
# 📦 build:      Build system or dependency changes
# 🔀 merge:      Merge commit

# ------------------

# Example commit message
# ✨ feat: Launch new feature
#
# Detailed description of the change
# Detailed description of the change
# Detailed description of the change
#
# Footer: Related issue: #123

# ------------------
# git config commit.template .commit_template
# Run the above command to set this as the default commit template
